cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with the problem of learning disentangled representations, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of variational auto-encoders and regularization techniques suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on image data and the use of convolutional neural networks suggests that it may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of deep learning techniques and the focus on improving reconstruction performance suggests that it may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques and the focus on improving the training step suggests that it may also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
